    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are positioned for a high-ceiling offensive output today, anchored by **Jackson Merrill** (74.85) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (74.84), who share the top honors in our daily projections. **Jackson Merrill** benefits significantly from leading off against Taillon, where his elite sprint speed\u2014a core priority for our roster\u2014pairs with an optimized order position to capitalize on run-scoring opportunities. Meanwhile, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** leverages a strong BvP history (31 PA) against Bello, paired with an favorable xwOBA of 0.384, making him our most reliable anchor. Also worth noting is **Gunnar Henderson** (73.38) and **Kyle Tucker** (73.39), both of whom are set up for massive days; **Gunnar Henderson** specifically benefits from a 16% park factor boost, while **Kyle Tucker** remains an elite foundational piece despite the tough assignment against Alcantara.\n\nThe decision-making process for the final utility spots necessitated difficult cuts, with **Josh Jung** (52.80) being the most difficult omission. While **Josh Jung** performed well in the simulation, he ultimately fell short of the threshold required to displace **Marcell Ozuna** (60.22). **Marcell Ozuna** earned the nod not only through a favorable matchup against Pallante, but due to a projected wind-out factor that adds significant home run potential to his profile. Elsewhere, we are closely monitoring the status of **Drake Baldwin**, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, and **Marcell Ozuna**, as their projections assume specific lineup slots; should they slide down the order, we will need to re-evaluate their efficiency scores. We are also proceeding with caution regarding **Heliot Ramos**, who remains on our bench with a 41.44 score; his 40% rain risk combined with a stiff matchup against Cristopher S\u00e1nchez makes him a liability we are content to sit for now. Our strategy remains clear: prioritize the high-upside speed threats like **Jacob Wilson** and **Josh Lowe** to maintain our competitive edge in the stolen base category while leveraging the power profiles of **Andy Pages** and **Miguel Vargas** to maximize RBI volume.",
